-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Bundled reference data — third-party attributions
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The Choupo SOURCE CODE is GPL-3.0-or-later (above).  The curated
reference data under `data/standards/` is an AGGREGATION of independently-licensed
datasets; each data file carries its own provenance header (primary source,
method, licence).  The third-party datasets bundled here, and their licences, are:

* UNIFAC group-contribution parameters (`data/standards/unifac/`) and selected
  pure-component constants / binary interaction parameters
  Compiled in the ChemSep database, (c) Harry Kooijman & Ross Taylor, under the
  Artistic License 2.0 (FSF-listed, GPL-compatible).  PRIMARY sources cited per
  table: original/VLE UNIFAC of Hansen, Rasmussen, Fredenslund, Schiller &
  Gmehling, Ind. Eng. Chem. Res. 30 (1991) 2352; DECHEMA VLE Data Collection.
  Imported by bin/curate/ into Choupo dict form (values unchanged; names
  tokenizer-sanitised).  The ChemSep simulator code is NOT used or bundled.

* Henry's-law constants (`data/standards/henrysLaw/`)
  Sander, R. (2015), "Compilation of Henry's law constants (version 4.0) for
  water as solvent," Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics 15, 4399-4981,
  doi:10.5194/acp-15-4399-2015.  Licensed CC-BY 3.0.
  Redistributed via the open-source `thermo` library (Caleb Bell, MIT-licensed
  code; the Sander data retains its CC-BY licence).  CHANGES: Sander's van't
  Hoff coefficients (ln H_xp[Pa] = A + B/T) were converted to Choupo's
  H_ref / enthalpy parameterisation; see each `*-water.dat` header.

* Pure-component reference-fluid data (part of `data/standards/components/`)
  Derived from CoolProp (Bell, Wronski, Quoilin & Lemort, 2014; MIT licence)
  high-accuracy Helmholtz equations of state.  Antoine and ideal-gas-Cp
  correlations were FITTED to the CoolProp reference curves; critical
  constants and acentric factors are reported facts.  See each file header
  for which fields are CoolProp-derived.

* Ingestion / provenance tooling
  The `chemicals` and `thermo` libraries (Caleb Bell, MIT licence) were used
  as the deterministic ingestion and provenance index.  Property ESTIMATES in
  some component files (formation, ideal-gas Cp) are computed by the Joback
  group-contribution method (Joback & Reid, 1987 — a published method, facts);
  such fields are tagged `[origin=estimated method=Joback]` and are intended
  for student review before reaction-critical use.

This product also bundles, with their respective licences honoured:
PubChem identifiers (U.S. public domain) and Wikidata facts (CC0).
Excluded by policy (not bundled): NIST SRD/WebBook, DIPPR, Yaws, CRC, DECHEMA/
DDBST, and any NonCommercial (e.g. CC-BY-NC) source.
